I agree on the name being confusing. The refactor you did on the other forLabel methods cleaned up the code nicely and I believe could further be reduced to one function for all of these classes. The Container class could have a protected static method that retrieves the xpath - something like: (pseudo code)
protected static getXpath(xOpt, container) {
    const itemXpath = xPathOptionToXpath(xOpt, container);
    await page.waitForXPath(itemXpath, {visible: true});
    return itemXpath
}

The forLabel (to be renamed) functions could then look like:
return new SelectMenu(page, await this.getXpath(xOpt, container))

Another option could be to have a generic xpath utility function outside of the class hierarchy that returns an xpath and these classes could be constructed directly

